<subSubSection id="C36A6504A46DFFABFCA8FD54FAABFC12" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCF368FA46DFFABFCA8FD54FAABFC12" blockId="12.[824,1476,652,900]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46DFFABFCA8FD54FC0CFD32" box="[862,925,653,676]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Notes.</emphasis>
– This species is found in the Guianas and Amazonian 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46DFFABFC9BFD75FC4AFD52" box="[877,987,684,708]" name="Venezuela" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46DFFABFC13FD75FBAEFD52" box="[997,1087,684,708]" name="Ecuador" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46DFFABFBBCFD74FBEDFD52" box="[1098,1148,685,708]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and northern 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46DFFABFAECFD75FACBFD52" box="[1306,1370,684,708]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA46DFFABFA9CFD75FCE5FD72" author="TAYLOR, C. M." pageId="12" pageNumber="301" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). See 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA46DFFABFC4EFD15FBF4FD72" author="TAYLOR, C. M." box="[952,1125,716,740]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR (2005)</bibRefCitation>
and DELPRETE &amp; KIRKBRIDE (2015) for synonymy. DELPRETE &amp; KIRKBRIDE (2015) reported that this species is found “throughout 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46DFFABFACEFCD5FAE6FCB2" box="[1336,1399,780,804]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Brazil</collectingCountry>
” but it seems to be restricted to the Amazon basin. 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46DFFABFAE5FCF5FCEBFCF2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="astrellantha">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46DFFABFAE5FCF5FCEBFCF2" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Eumachia astrellantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has often been confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46DFFABFB34FC94FACCFCF2" box="[1218,1373,844,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaenotricha">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46DFFABFB34FC94FACCFCF2" box="[1218,1373,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">E. chaenotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is found widely in eastern and southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46DFFABFB02FCB5FAA7FC12" box="[1268,1334,876,900]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
